article.headline: Arkansas St. 74, E. Illinois 60
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrian Banks scored 22 points, including three 3-pointers, to lead Arkansas State to a 74-60 win Saturday night over Eastern Illinois. Banks' effort, as well as 18 points by fellow guard Ryan Wedel, clinched the win for Arkansas State (3-3). No other Indians player broke double digits in the game, though the team shot 50 percent from the floor. Arkansas State also netted nine steals from the Panthers, who turned the ball over 18 times during the game. Eastern Illinois (3-3) saw guard Romain Martin score 21 points during the game, including hitting three 3-pointers. Guard Julio Anthony put up 12 points as the Panthers as a whole made 46 percent of their shots.
